race.comment: Competitive. ACTION KING (4) switched from a Brisbane yard and looked a run short in Open grade at Dubbo. Brought strong provincial and metro form to that and is proven second-up. Has the inside gate and is well placed to win. REBEL DEAN (5) raced three times in town before his nose defeat at Moruya in Open grade behind TAKE THE RAP. Day sticks aboard and will likely push forward again. Ready to win. TAKE THE RAP (2) deserved the Moruya win returning to his best. The gate is a little awkward but he looks capable of going back-to-back. SUTTON VELLA (11) needs some luck in the run but tumbles 6kg off her 66 win at Cootamundra. That brings her right into it and she has a strong record this track/trip.
